Reasoning: The paper presents a framework based on recent advances in deep learning for seismic phase association. The approach is trained entirely on synthetic data generated using a 1-D velocity model. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the real-time processing and automated processing of large seismic data sets, which suggests that it could also belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the potential impact of the approach on seismicity catalogs, which suggests that it could also belong to the Sound (cs.SD) sub-category.
